      "writtenOn": "2017-01-30T19:20:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So in this current change, I move both ctors and the flags to protected. From what I can tell only subclasses will every explicitly use the flags when calling the parents ctor. Besides that we have functions like isDrawVulkanSupported() to query for support. What virtual is needed here? This leaves the API in a state where the user doesn\u0027t need to know that we\u0027re tracking capabilities with flags versus some other method.",
